# Project Structure Guide

## Directory Structure

This Next.js application follows a well-organized structure:

- [app/](mdc:app) - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- [components/](mdc:components) - Reusable UI components
  - [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui) - shadcn/ui base components
- [hooks/](mdc:hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [services/](mdc:services) - API and business logic services
- [store/](mdc:store) - State management (Zustand)
- [lib/](mdc:lib) - Utility functions and helpers
- [types/](mdc:types) - TypeScript type definitions
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets

## Key Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - shadcn/ui configuration
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component
- [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Global CSS styles
